This paper is primarily focused on the problem of incentivizing credible sample contributions from self-interested agents for building data-intensive learning systems. This problem is closely related to the field of machine learning, particularly deep learning, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the design of an incentive-compatible score function, which is a topic of interest in game theory and mechanism design, falling under the category of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper introduces a deep learning aided method, which is a topic of interest in the field of artificial intelligence, falling under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the estimation of a certain function, which is a topic of interest in information theory, falling under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper involves numerical experiments, which involve the use of algorithms and data structures, falling under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
